CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 5, 1960, pg. A18, reads: "Hill Top Scouts Hold Dinner - A Blue and Gold Dinner, celebrating 50 years of scouting was held recently by the Hill Top Scouts at the Knoxville YMCA. The highlight of the evening was the presentation of a plaque of appreciation by Harold Griffin, center, director of Hill City, to Cubmaster Sam Jennings.  Some of the members of the Scout troop are, left to right: Jackie James, Darreyl Hickman, Jerry Williams, William Stephens and Ronald Harris. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Cub Scouts from Pittsburgh Troop 545, and Beltzhoover Troop 20, from left: Jack James, Darryl Hickman, Scout Master Sam Jennings holding plaque inscribed "In grateful recognition to services rendered in Cub Scouting" with Harold Griffin, Jerry Williams standing in back, William "Bucky" Stephens, and Ronald "Ronnie" Harris, in Knoxville YMCA
